    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "#Event Triggers \r\nAn event trigger is a way to control when a sound plays during your performance. By pressing number keys (1-9), you can trigger a new chunk of code to run immediately, on the next beat, or at the next measure, allowing you to add sounds real time.\r\n\r\nUse this backtrack to get started. Find sounds that layer well on top of it. \r\n\r\n**Do This:**\r\n- Use `1 triggered immediately` to trigger a sound effect to play with this backbeat. \r\n- Use  `2 triggered at next beat` to trigger a new drum and bass sound to layer onto the backbeat. \r\n- Use `3 triggered at next measure` to make a short, 4-measure loop for even more layering of sounds. ",
